    "⭐ ddtScheme<Type> is the abstract base class for all time derivative schemes in OpenFOAM.",
    "⭐ Key concrete schemes include: Euler (first-order), backward (second-order), CrankNicolson (second-order).",
    "⭐ The Euler implicit scheme uses the first-order formula: (phi^n - phi^(n-1)) / Delta t.",
    "⭐ For the fvm::ddt operator, the Euler scheme contributes a diagonal coefficient: rho_P * V_P / Delta t.",
    "⭐ The backward (BDF2) second-order scheme uses the previous two time steps: phi^(n-1) and phi^(n-2).",
    "⭐ The Crank-Nicolson scheme uses an off-centering coefficient (ocCoeff) to improve stability.",
    "⭐ The Courant (CFL) number is defined as CFL = |u| * Delta t / Delta x.",
